cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.GT 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it analyzes the behavior of players in a casual online game and draws conclusions about the relationship between performance and practice. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it studies the behavior of many players and their interactions within the game. Additionally, the use of an epsilon-machine and hidden Markov model suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's discussion of psychological findings about persistence and grit could place it in the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
